Burton’s (1928)
deep-water record of 

Gellius flagellifer

from the nearby Andaman Sea was possibly the present species, as the upper size of the normal sigmas falls within the variation of the above measurements. However, the oxeas of the Andaman specimens are 280–360 × 12–14 μm, well in excess of those measured above. Combined with the deepwater occurrence (
300–900 m
) the conspecificity appears doubtful.
